SVG Stroke Animation with CSS (WAAPI too)

The other day I used Anime.js V4 to make an SVG stroke animation. Awesome as that animation library is, it was overkill for what I created. Turns out we can achieve the same effect with modern CSS alone!

I'm using animation-timeline: scroll(), which doesn't work for folks on Firefox and Safari, so for you the effect is revealed on hover.

As a bonus(?) I also have a basic WAAPI implementation in the JS, commented out for now. It can achieve the same effect via CSS animations and much more! like being able to listen for when the CSS animation finishes (For example).

This SVG stroke animation relies on knowing the length of the path. This can be a hard-coded value, but for convenience I've obtained and set that via JS.

Credits

  • WAAPI MDN Docs - I'm just getting started with the Web Animations API, but these docs helped a lot.
  • Sara Soueidan - For their SVG Filter Effects article, which I followed to create a paper-like texture for the layers.
